		[1343] heading 'Apple Footer'
		[1344] region 'Footnotes'
			[1345] list ''
				[1346] listitem ''
					StaticText '1. Hearing\xa0Aid and Hearing\xa0Test: The Hearing\xa0Aid feature has received FDA authorization. The Hearing\xa0Test and Hearing\xa0Aid features are supported on AirPods\xa0Pro\xa02 with the latest firmware paired with a compatible iPhone or iPad with iOS\xa018 or iPadOS\xa018 and later and are intended for people 18 years old or older. The Hearing Aid feature is also supported on a compatible Mac with macOS\xa0Sequoia and later. It is intended for people with perceived mild to moderate hearing\xa0loss.'
					StaticText 'Hearing\xa0Protection: The Hearing\xa0Protection feature works with AirPods\xa0Pro\xa02 with the latest firmware when paired with a compatible iPhone, iPad, or Mac with iOS\xa018, iPadOS\xa018, or macOS\xa0Sequoia and later. Feature is only available in the U.S. and Canada. See'
					[1350] link'support.apple.com/120850', clickable, url='https://support.apple.com/120850'
					StaticText 'for total attenuation and more information. The Hearing\xa0Protection feature is not suitable for protection against extremely loud impulse sounds, such as gunfire, fireworks, or jackhammers, or against sustained sounds louder than 110\xa0dBA.'
				[1351] listitem ''
					StaticText '2. Available in two models: AirPods\xa04 and AirPods\xa04 with Active\xa0Noise\xa0Cancellation.'
				[1353] listitem ''
					StaticText '3. Trade‑in values will vary based on the condition, year, and configuration of your eligible trade‑in device. Not all devices are eligible for credit. You must be at least the age of majority to be eligible to trade in for credit or for an Apple\xa0Gift\xa0Card. Trade‑in value may be applied toward qualifying new device purchase, or added to an Apple\xa0Gift\xa0Card. Actual value awarded is based on receipt of a qualifying device matching the description provided when estimate was made. Sales tax may be assessed on full value of a new device purchase. In‑store trade‑in requires presentation of a valid photo ID (local law may require saving this information). Offer may not be available in all stores, and may vary between in‑store and online trade‑in. Some stores may have additional requirements. Apple or its trade‑in partners reserve the right to refuse, cancel, or limit quantity of any trade‑in transaction for any reason. More details are available from Apple’s trade-in partner for trade‑in and recycling of eligible devices. Restrictions and limitations may\xa0apply.'
				[1357] listitem ''
					StaticText 'Apple\xa0Intelligence is available in beta on all iPhone\xa016 models, iPhone\xa015\xa0Pro, iPhone\xa015\xa0Pro\xa0Max, iPad\xa0mini (A17\xa0Pro), and iPad and Mac models with M1 and later, with Siri and device language set to English (Australia, Canada, Ireland, New Zealand, South Africa, UK, or U.S.), as part of an iOS\xa018, iPadOS\xa018, and macOS\xa0Sequoia software update. Additional features and languages will be available in April, with more languages coming over the course of the year. Languages supported in 2025 include Chinese, English (India, Singapore), French, German, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Portuguese, Spanish, and\xa0Vietnamese.'
				[1358] listitem ''
					StaticText 'A subscription is required for Apple\xa0Arcade, Apple\xa0Fitness+, Apple\xa0Music, and Apple\xa0TV+.'
				[1360] listitem ''
					StaticText 'Features are subject to change. Some features, applications, and services may not be available in all regions or all languages.'

			[1345] list ''
				[1346] listitem ''
					StaticText '1. Hearing\xa0Aid and Hearing\xa0Test: The Hearing\xa0Aid feature has received FDA authorization. The Hearing\xa0Test and Hearing\xa0Aid features are supported on AirPods\xa0Pro\xa02 with the latest firmware paired with a compatible iPhone or iPad with iOS\xa018 or iPadOS\xa018 and later and are intended for people 18 years old or older. The Hearing Aid feature is also supported on a compatible Mac with macOS\xa0Sequoia and later. It is intended for people with perceived mild to moderate hearing\xa0loss.'
					StaticText 'Hearing\xa0Protection: The Hearing\xa0Protection feature works with AirPods\xa0Pro\xa02 with the latest firmware when paired with a compatible iPhone, iPad, or Mac with iOS\xa018, iPadOS\xa018, or macOS\xa0Sequoia and later. Feature is only available in the U.S. and Canada. See'
					[1350] link'support.apple.com/120850', clickable, url='https://support.apple.com/120850'
					StaticText 'for total attenuation and more information. The Hearing\xa0Protection feature is not suitable for protection against extremely loud impulse sounds, such as gunfire, fireworks, or jackhammers, or against sustained sounds louder than 110\xa0dBA.'
				[1351] listitem ''
					StaticText '2. Available in two models: AirPods\xa04 and AirPods\xa04 with Active\xa0Noise\xa0Cancellation.'
				[1353] listitem ''
					StaticText '3. Trade‑in values will vary based on the condition, year, and configuration of your eligible trade‑in device. Not all devices are eligible for credit. You must be at least the age of majority to be eligible to trade in for credit or for an Apple\xa0Gift\xa0Card. Trade‑in value may be applied toward qualifying new device purchase, or added to an Apple\xa0Gift\xa0Card. Actual value awarded is based on receipt of a qualifying device matching the description provided when estimate was made. Sales tax may be assessed on full value of a new device purchase. In‑store trade‑in requires presentation of a valid photo ID (local law may require saving this information). Offer may not be available in all stores, and may vary between in‑store and online trade‑in. Some stores may have additional requirements. Apple or its trade‑in partners reserve the right to refuse, cancel, or limit quantity of any trade‑in transaction for any reason. More details are available from Apple’s trade-in partner for trade‑in and recycling of eligible devices. Restrictions and limitations may\xa0apply.'
				[1357] listitem ''
					StaticText 'Apple\xa0Intelligence is available in beta on all iPhone\xa016 models, iPhone\xa015\xa0Pro, iPhone\xa015\xa0Pro\xa0Max, iPad\xa0mini (A17\xa0Pro), and iPad and Mac models with M1 and later, with Siri and device language set to English (Australia, Canada, Ireland, New Zealand, South Africa, UK, or U.S.), as part of an iOS\xa018, iPadOS\xa018, and macOS\xa0Sequoia software update. Additional features and languages will be available in April, with more languages coming over the course of the year. Languages supported in 2025 include Chinese, English (India, Singapore), French, German, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Portuguese, Spanish, and\xa0Vietnamese.'
				[1358] listitem ''
					StaticText 'A subscription is required for Apple\xa0Arcade, Apple\xa0Fitness+, Apple\xa0Music, and Apple\xa0TV+.'
				[1360] listitem ''
					StaticText 'Features are subject to change. Some features, applications, and services may not be available in all regions or all languages.'

					StaticText 'A subscription is required for Apple\xa0Fitness+. Apple\xa0Fitness+ requires iPhone\xa08 or later, or Apple\xa0Watch Series\xa03 or later paired with an iPhone\xa06s or later.'
				[1357] listitem ''
					StaticText '2. Trade‑in values will vary based on the condition, year, and configuration of your eligible trade‑in device. Not all devices are eligible for credit. Actual value awarded is based on receipt of a qualifying device matching the description provided when estimate was made. Sales tax may be assessed on full value of a new device purchase. In‑store trade‑in requires presentation of a valid photo ID (local law may require saving this information). Offer may not be available in all stores, and may vary between in‑store and online trade‑in. Some stores may have additional requirements. Apple or its trade‑in partners reserve the right to refuse, cancel, or limit quantity of any trade‑in transaction for any reason. More details are available from Apple’s trade-in partner for trade‑in and recycling of eligible devices. Restrictions and limitations may\xa0apply.'
				[1359] listitem ''
					StaticText 'To access and use all Apple\xa0Card features and products available only to Apple\xa0Card users, you must add Apple\xa0Card to Wallet on an iPhone or iPad that supports and has the latest version of iOS or iPadOS. 		[1344] region 'Footnotes'
			[1345] list ''
				[1346] listitem ''
					StaticText '1. Hearing\xa0Aid and Hearing\xa0Test: The Hearing\xa0Aid feature has received FDA authorization. The Hearing\xa0Test and Hearing\xa0Aid features are supported on AirPods\xa0Pro\xa02 with the latest firmware paired with a compatible iPhone or iPad with iOS\xa018 or iPadOS\xa018 and later and are intended for people 18 years old or older. The Hearing Aid feature is also supported on a compatible Mac with macOS\xa0Sequoia and later. It is intended for people with perceived mild to moderate hearing\xa0loss.'
					StaticText 'Hearing\xa0Protection: The Hearing\xa0Protection feature works with AirPods\xa0Pro\xa02 with the latest firmware when paired with a compatible iPhone, iPad, or Mac with iOS\xa018, iPadOS\xa018, or macOS\xa0Sequoia and later. Feature is only available in the U.S. and Canada. See'
					[1350] link'support.apple.com/120850', clickable, url='https://support.apple.com/120850'
					StaticText 'for total attenuation and more information. The Hearing\xa0Protection feature is not suitable for protection against extremely loud impulse sounds, such as gunfire, fireworks, or jackhammers, or against sustained sounds louder than 110\xa0dBA.'
				[1351] listitem ''
					StaticText '2. Available in two models: AirPods\xa04 and AirPods\xa04 with Active\xa0Noise\xa0Cancellation.'
				[1353] listitem ''
					StaticText '3. Trade‑in values will vary based on the condition, year, and configuration of your eligible trade‑in device. Not all devices are eligible for credit. You must be at least the age of majority to be eligible to trade in for credit or for an Apple\xa0Gift\xa0Card. Trade‑in value may be applied toward qualifying new device purchase, or added to an Apple\xa0Gift\xa0Card. Actual value awarded is based on receipt of a qualifying device matching the description provided when estimate was made. Sales tax may be assessed on full value of a new device purchase. In‑store trade‑in requires presentation of a valid photo ID (local law may require saving this information). Offer may not be available in all stores, and may vary between in‑store and online trade‑in. Some stores may have additional requirements. Apple or its trade‑in partners reserve the right to refuse, cancel, or limit quantity of any trade‑in transaction for any reason. More details are available from Apple’s trade-in partner for trade‑in and recycling of eligible devices. Restrictions and limitations may\xa0apply.'
				[1357] listitem ''
					StaticText 'Apple\xa0Intelligence is available in beta on all iPhone\xa016 models, iPhone\xa015\xa0Pro, iPhone\xa015\xa0Pro\xa0Max, iPad\xa0mini (A17\xa0Pro), and iPad and Mac models with M1 and later, with Siri and device language set to English (Australia, Canada, Ireland, New Zealand, South Africa, UK, or U.S.), as part of an iOS\xa018, iPadOS\xa018, and macOS\xa0Sequoia software update. Additional features and languages will be available in April, with more languages coming over the course of the year. Languages supported in 2025 include Chinese, English (India, Singapore), French, German, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Portuguese, Spanish, and\xa0Vietnamese.'
				[1358] listitem ''
					StaticText 'A subscription is required for Apple\xa0Arcade, Apple\xa0Fitness+, Apple\xa0Music, and Apple\xa0TV+.'
				[1360] listitem ''
					StaticText 'Features are subject to change. Some features, applications, and services may not be available in all regions or all languages.'
